# .env.example — onchain-intel secrets template (ADR-001 D10)
#
# Copy this file to `.env` in the repo root and fill in real values there. `.env` must
# be created with permissions 0600 (`chmod 600 .env`) and is NEVER committed — it is
# already excluded via .gitignore (`.env`, `.env.*`, with `.env.example` explicitly
# un-ignored). This file intentionally holds NO real secret values, only the convention.
#
#   chmod 600 .env
#
# As of M0 there are no required environment variables: the env-validation module
# (packages/mcp-server/src/env.ts, added in task 001-2) validates an empty environment
# successfully (cost ladder: M0-M1 run at $0, no provider keys needed yet). Future
# provider API keys (Nansen, Dune, Bitquery, ...) will be documented here as they are
# introduced in M1+.
